PLANTS OF SOUTH CAROLINA
Lexington County

*Galax aphylla* L.

*Galax aphylla* and *Isotria verticillata* common along
sandstone outcrops along the headwaters of Hunt
Branch. From intersection of SC 6 and Lexington Co
65 take former 0.2 miles NW. Walk NE 0.2 miles
following stream bed cutting a deep ravine.
Mountain laurel extremely dense and covering rocks
and side slopes. *Galax* patches mainly confined to
long strips between rock outcrops and stream bed.
33.8099N & 81.204W

AB Pittman 10079907  07 Oct. 1999 _(handwritten)_
A.R. Darr
